text: Mattubby Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Mattubby is a name derived from the Chickasaw language purported to mean "the one who kills all". Variant names are "Mattuby Creek", "Matubba Creek", "Matubbie Creek", and "Matubby Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Chickasaw County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Monroe County, Mississippi
